node.text: The morning fog in Washington is very much alive....🌿. I could sit here and watch it all day.
Guess who had the whole beach to herself?
If you were to ask me if there's anything I love more than the PNW fog and trees, my answer would be no. Or maybe pizza.
Saw wild dolphins playing in San Diego bay :) so cool!
I wish all the people I love could enjoy this with me.
Enjoying the last bit of Washington summer.
#Washington
Washington is SO ugly
Most beautiful drive
I can't wink
Take a break :) woke up early for this.
The ugliest place

node.text: Chasing hot air balloons and desert skies 🏜🎈. Spent the last week exploring Phoenix, AZ and man was it hot 🥵. Some days reaching almost 118 degrees! Sunrise definitely became my favorite time of day because that was when it was only 90 degrees 😂. Seeing these balloons float over the Sonoran Desert was definitely worth the 3am wake up call ✨ @visitphoenix @hotairexpeditions

node.text: Have spent the past 2 days exploring Sedona with @polarisadventures for National Get Outside Day. It was so nice to disconnect with my phone and reconnect with nature ✨. Saw so many amazing places and beautiful red rocks 😍. I love Arizona and all it’s natural beauty—and exploring it with a RZR is truly the best way to see it all 🏜#polarisadventures #offliner #sedonaatv

node.text: There’s nothing quite like the textures of the waves ✨🌊. I have been really unmotivated by Instagram for a long time. I shoot all the time but never share my work here because I get so caught up in the numbers and feeling disappointed if my work is not received well. I hate to admit that — but it’s true! And lately I’ve been trying not to be so self critical and just share because I love it. Might not happen over night, but I miss the community of this app 🤍. Thank you all for always being so kind to me ✨
